    <TITLE>SendMessage Specification</TITLE>
  </HEAD>
  <BODY TEXT="black" BGCOLOR="#f0f0f0">

    <PRE>
Module leafname...
  SendMsg

Module title...
  SendMessage

Module *Commands...

  *SendMessage [-udp | -tcp] [-destination <destination>] [-quiet] -message "<message text>"

  or

  *SendMessage [-u | -t] [-d <destination>] [-q] -m "<message text>"

    -udp            Use UDP/IP
    -tcp            Use TCP/IP
    <destination>   <hostname or dotted-quad IP address>:<port number or name>
    -quiet          Exit and do not report any errors
    <message text>  ctrl-terminated string, enclosed in double quotes

    If no protocol is specified, then use SendMessage$Protocol
    If if both protocols are specified, then use TCP
    If -destination not specified, then use SendMessage$Destination
    If SendMessage$Quiet is set, then always work in 'quiet' mode

  This command will attempt to squirt the specified textual string down a socket which
  has been opened to the specified port of the specified IP address. It will then close
  the socket once the string has been sent.

  Examples...

    *SendMessage -message "This is a message"
    *SendMessage -tcp -d earth.eng.cam.pace.co.uk:telnet -quiet -m "login"
    *SendMessage -u -d 136.170.128.60:55555 -q -m "This is a silly string"

Module service calls...

  None.
    </PRE>
  </BODY>
</HTML>
